    <div class="form-container">
        <div class="header">
            <div class="irs-logo">IRS</div>
            <div class="dept-title">Department of the Treasury<br>Internal Revenue Service</div>
        </div>

        <h1>Publication 550-T (2024)<br>Tax Liability for High-Volume Securities Traders</h1>

        <p>This publication provides guidance for individuals who trade securities as a business. If your trading
            activity is frequent, regular, and continuous, you may qualify for <strong>Trader Tax Status (TTS)</strong>.
        </p>

        <div class="section-title">The Wash Sale Rule (Section 1091)</div>
        <p>For most investors, a "wash sale" occurs when you sell a security at a loss and buy a "substantially
            identical" security within 30 days before or after the sale. The loss is disallowed for the current tax year
            and added to the basis of the new position.</p>

        <div class="warning-box">
            <strong>CAUTION:</strong> Avid traders often trigger thousands of wash sales, potentially resulting in a
            massive tax bill even if the net account value decreased.
        </div>

        <div class="section-title">Interactive Liability Evaluator</div>
        <div class="interactive-tool">
            <p><em>Determine if your trading activity meets the "Trader" threshold or remains "Investor" status.</em>
            </p>

            <label for="trades">Average trades per month:</label>
            <input type="number" id="trades" placeholder="e.g., 50">

            <label for="holding">Average holding period (days):</label>
            <input type="number" id="holding" placeholder="e.g., 2">

            <label for="intent">Primary intent of trading:</label>
            <select id="intent">
                <option value="income">Daily Income / Short-term swings</option>
                <option value="growth">Long-term Capital Appreciation</option>
            </select>

            <button onclick="evaluateStatus()">Run Compliance Check</button>
            <div id="audit-result"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-title">Mark-to-Market Election (Section 475(f))</div>
        <p>Qualified traders may elect to use the mark-to-market method of accounting. Under this method:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Gains and losses are treated as ordinary income/loss.</li>
            <li>The <strong>Wash Sale Rule does not apply</strong>.</li>
            <li>The $3,000 capital loss limitation is waived.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><em>Note: Election must be filed by April 15th of the prior tax year.</em></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        function evaluateStatus() {
            const trades = document.getElementById('trades').value;
            const holding = document.getElementById('holding').value;
            const intent = document.getElementById('intent').value;
            const result = document.getElementById('audit-result');

            result.style.display = "block";

            if (trades >= 30 && holding <= 30 && intent === 'income') {
                result.innerHTML = "DETERMINATION: Potential Trader Tax Status (TTS). You may qualify for Section 179 deductions and Schedule C expense reporting. Consider Section 475(f) election for next cycle.";
                result.style.color = "#006400";
                result.style.backgroundColor = "#e6fffa";
            } else {
                result.innerHTML = "DETERMINATION: Investor Status. You are subject to the $3,000 net capital loss limitation and strict Wash Sale rules. Report all activity on Form 8949 and Schedule D.";
                result.style.color = "#b22222";
                result.style.backgroundColor = "#fff5f5";
            }
        }
    </script>

